What Guests Said About Châtel-Guyon:




Andrew
United Kingdom











6.0


Must revisit in season

I was not there for a holiday.  It was work despite my welcome hour in the hotel spa.  The town was not at its best in February due to weather and being out of (spa) season.  The spa season for the town commences late March.Shopkeepers friendly.Excellent 4 course 35 Euros dinner at Villa M recommended.








Hotels That Guests Love in Châtel-Guyon





Hôtel Spa Thermalia









“Warm and responsive. We had a wonderful time. I highly recommend this hotel.”







Hôtel Spa Thermalia









“Very warm welcome from the lovely and helpful staff.  The hotel has been recently renovated and everything is in good shape and very clean.  Enjoyed the pool as well.”







Hôtel Spa Thermalia









“Very friendly owner, Robert, and helpful receptionist, Jeanette.  Hotel was busy due to a conference and a celebrity guest but we were made to feel welcome guests.  Very comfortable bedrooms.  Nice spa-sauna, steam room and jacuzzi.This was a business trip but would gladly return for a short leisure break.Robert kindly arranged a taxi both ways from nearest railway station, Riom-Chatel Guyon, 6 kms away.”








